trend_summary: Across the sequence, the southwestern city spreads outward and infills, while most surrounding land remains agricultural. Several hamlets grow slightly along roads, cropland blocks consolidate, and riparian green strips widen. Overall built-up footprint rises slowly but still occupies a small share of the territory, keeping the landscape largely rural.
notable_changes: Gradual outward expansion and densification of the southwestern urban core.
New or widened bypass/road links connecting villages, encouraging ribbon development.
Small clusters of new housing appear along the main river corridor.
Noticeable consolidation of cropland parcels; fewer fallow patches.
Broader green belts and tree cover increase along waterways and field margins.
